  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>Get all your ingredients and equipment ready</p><p>Skim through these steps, then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Note: Equipment and pan sizes vary. Make sure you cook food thoroughly (even if it takes you a little longer than 10 min)</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/chinese-style-fable-mushroom-braise-with-pak-choi/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Boil half a kettle</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>fable pulled mushrooms</strong> and cook for an initial 4-5 min or until beginning to char</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/chinese-style-fable-mushroom-braise-with-pak-choi/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely slice your <strong>shallot[s]</strong></p><p>Wash your <strong>pak choi</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Cut the<strong> pak choi </strong>in half, separating the <strong>white base </strong>and <strong>green tops</strong></p><p>Cut the <strong>white base </strong>into bite-sized pieces</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/chinese-style-fable-mushroom-braise-with-pak-choi/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the fable pulled mushrooms are charred, reduce the heat to medium-high</p><p>Add the <strong>sliced shallot</strong>,<strong> chilli flakes </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!), <strong>ginger & garlic paste</strong> and 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span><strong> flour</strong> and cook for 30 secs or until fragrant</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/chinese-style-fable-mushroom-braise-with-pak-choi/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, add your <strong>soy sauce</strong>, 150ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[200ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[250ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>and<strong> rice vinegar</strong></p><p>Add your<strong> hoisin sauce</strong>,<strong> tomato paste</strong>, <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong>, 1/2 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3/4 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[1 tsp] </span><strong>sugar </strong>and a very generous grind of <strong>black pepper</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/chinese-style-fable-mushroom-braise-with-pak-choi/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped pak choi </strong>and<strong> whole leaves</strong> to the pan and cook, covered, for 2-3 min or until the pak choi is tender and the sauce has thickened – this is your<strong> Chinese-style fable mushroom braise</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/chinese-style-fable-mushroom-braise-with-pak-choi/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Squeeze your pouch[es]<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>of <strong>cooked white long grain rice </strong>to separate the grains</p><p>Tear the top corner of the pouch[es]<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>(just a little!) and <strong>microwave</strong> for 2 min or until piping hot</p><p>Tip: If you're cooking two or more pouches, pop them in together but increase the microwave cook time accordingly</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/chinese-style-fable-mushroom-braise-with-pak-choi/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>Chinese-style fable mushroom braise</strong> with the <strong>cooked rice</strong> to the side</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
